                      "fill": "#A1A1AA",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "The Atlanta Dogwood Festival is one of Atlanta's oldest and most beloved traditions, celebrating spring in Piedmont Park since 1936. The three-day festival features live music on multiple stages, over 250 fine artists and craftspeople, an artist market, food vendors from Atlanta's best restaurants, a kids' village, and the famous disc dog competition. Admission is free.",
